==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Melanoscope
<hw>Me*lan"o*scope</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr.
<grk>me`las</grk>, <grk>me`lanos</grk>, black +
<ets>-scope</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Opt.)</fld> <def>An instrument
containing a combination of colored glasses such that they transmit only
red light, so that objects of other colors, as green leaves, appear
black when seen through it. It is used for viewing colored flames, to
detect the presence of potassium, lithium, etc., by the red light which
they emit.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Melanosis</ent>⟦br⟧
\'d8
